### HINet: Half Instance Normalization Network for Image Restoration

**Weblink:**  
https://github.com/megvii-model/HINet

#### Overview
**HINet (Half Instance Normalization Network)** is a deep learning model proposed for image restoration tasks. It introduces half instance normalization to improve feature representation while preserving image details, making it effective for restoration problems such as denoising and enhancement.

#### Implementation Details
This implementation is based on **BasicSR**, an open-source toolbox for image and video restoration tasks.

**BasicSR Repository:**  
https://github.com/xinntao/BasicSR

#### Installation Requirements
- Python **3.6.9**  
- PyTorch **1.5.1**  
- CUDA **10.1**

